### Problem 4: Gmail SMTP Authentication Fails

#### 🔴 **Symptoms**
```
javax.mail.AuthenticationFailedException: 535-5.7.8 Username and Password not accepted
```
- Jenkins pipeline succeeds
- No email notifications received
- System log shows authentication errors

#### 🔍 **Root Cause**
Google blocks "less secure app access" by default. Standard password authentication is rejected even if credentials are correct.

#### ✅ **Solution: Use Gmail App Passwords**

**Step 1: Enable 2-Factor Authentication**
1. Go to Google Account: https://myaccount.google.com
2. Security → 2-Step Verification
3. Follow setup wizard
4. ⚠️ **Required:** You cannot create App Passwords without 2FA enabled

**Step 2: Generate App Password**
1. Go to: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
2. Or: Google Account → Security → App passwords
3. Select app: **Mail**
4. Select device: **Other (Custom name)**
5. Enter name: `Jenkins DevSecOps Pipeline`
6. Click **Generate**
7. **Copy the 16-character password** (format: `xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx`)
8. ⚠️ **Important:** You won't see this password again!

**Step 3: Configure Jenkins Email**

1. **Add Credentials:**
   - Manage Jenkins → Manage Credentials
   - Click **(global)** → Add Credentials
   - Kind: **Username with password**
   - Username: `your-email@gmail.com`
   - Password: **Paste the 16-character App Password** (remove spaces)
   - ID: `gmail-smtp`
   - Description: `Gmail SMTP for Notifications`

2. **Configure Email System:**
   - Manage Jenkins → Configure System
   - Scroll to **Extended E-mail Notification**
   
   ```
   SMTP server: smtp.gmail.com
   SMTP Port: 465
   Credentials: Select "gmail-smtp"
   ☑ Use SSL
   Default user e-mail suffix: @gmail.com
   ```

3. **Test Configuration:**
   - Check **"Test configuration by sending test e-mail"**
   - Test e-mail recipient: `your-email@gmail.com`
   - Click **Test configuration**
   - Should show: "Email was successfully sent"

**Step 4: Add to Jenkinsfile**
```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any
    
    environment {
        EMAIL_RECIPIENT = 'your-email@gmail.com'
    }
    
    stages {
        // ... your stages
    }
    
    post {
        success {
            emailext (
                to: "${EMAIL_RECIPIENT}",
                subject: "✅ Build SUCCESS: ${env.JOB_NAME} #${env.BUILD_NUMBER}",
                body: """
                    Build Status: SUCCESS
                    Job: ${env.JOB_NAME}
                    Build Number: ${env.BUILD_NUMBER}
                    
                    View details: ${env.BUILD_URL}
                """,
                mimeType: 'text/plain'
            )
        }
        
        failure {
            emailext (
                to: "${EMAIL_RECIPIENT}",
                subject: "❌ Build FAILED: ${env.JOB_NAME} #${env.BUILD_NUMBER}",
                body: """
                    Build Status: FAILED
                    Job: ${env.JOB_NAME}
                    Build Number: ${env.BUILD_NUMBER}
                    
                    Check logs: ${env.BUILD_URL}console
                """,
                mimeType: 'text/plain'
            )
        }
    }
}
```

#### 📧 **Email Template Best Practices**

**Include These Details:**
- ✅ Build status (SUCCESS/FAILURE)
- ✅ Job name and build number
- ✅ Direct link to build
- ✅ Timestamp
- ✅ Changed files (for failures)

**Example Advanced Template:**
```groovy
emailext (
    to: "${EMAIL_RECIPIENT}",
    subject: "${env.BUILD_STATUS}: ${env.JOB_NAME} - Build #${env.BUILD_NUMBER}",
    body: """
        <html>
        <body style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">
            <h2 style="color: ${env.BUILD_STATUS == 'SUCCESS' ? 'green' : 'red'};">
                Build ${env.BUILD_STATUS}
            </h2>
            <table>
                <tr><td><b>Job:</b></td><td>${env.JOB_NAME}</td></tr>
                <tr><td><b>Build:</b></td><td>#${env.BUILD_NUMBER}</td></tr>
                <tr><td><b>Duration:</b></td><td>${currentBuild.durationString}</td></tr>
                <tr><td><b>Started:</b></td><td>${new Date(currentBuild.startTimeInMillis)}</td></tr>
            </table>
            <p><a href="${env.BUILD_URL}">View Build Details</a></p>
            <p><a href="${env.BUILD_URL}console">View Console Output</a></p>
        </body>
        </html>
    """,
    mimeType: 'text/html'
)
```

#### 🔐 **Security Notes**

1. **App Password vs Regular Password**
   - App Password: 16 characters, works for automation
   - Regular Password: Won't work even if 2FA is off

2. **Revoke Access**
   - Go to Google Account → Security → App passwords
   - Find "Jenkins DevSecOps Pipeline"
   - Click Remove

3. **Multiple Environments**
   - Create separate App Passwords for Dev/Staging/Prod
   - Easier to revoke if one environment is compromised

